 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To Lady H—r, who ask'd, Had the Author done writing Verses?</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">me, my Patroness, and Friend,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can Age  Heights ascend?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sweet Poesy's light Footsteps trace?</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ah no! I must give up the Chace:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When Time the Head hath silver'd o'er,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The dear Delusion charms no more.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">why hast thou, with Taste endow'd,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">At Altar never bow'd?</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Shall Books engross thee all the Day?</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When, lo! he waits to grace thy Lay.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
